// @test regression/INV074-leading-operator-multiple-of-4-indent
// @description Leading operators on a wrapped expression line whose indent is a multiple of four are TV's CE10013-style mismatched input error anchored at the operator, but the parser still joins for recovery. The non-multiple-of-4 switch-arm continuation case is covered separately by INV073. See TODO #45.
// @expects parse: fail
// @expects error: line=5, message=/Mismatched input "\?" expecting "end of line without line continuation"/
// @expects error: line=6, message=/Mismatched input ":" expecting "end of line without line continuation"/
// @expects error: line=8, message=/Mismatched input "and" expecting "end of line without line continuation"/
//@version=6
indicator("x")
cond = close > open
float x = cond
    ? high
    : low
bool y = close > open
    and high > low
plot(x)
plot(y ? 1 : 0)
